captions.text:
-Oh, I assumed you're all crabs,
'cause you all sound so crabby!

Oh, wait. I got one.
Hey, hey, Orange,

-I just think it's easy
to see the bright side

when you have a rainbow
making your side bright.

-Well, you see,
my father was a trout

and my mom was
an actual rainbow,

so that's kind of why
I turned out the way I did.

-My great-great-grandmother
was a Double Stuf Oreo.

their great-great grandmother
was a Double Stuf Oreo?

-MY great-great-grandmother
was a Double Stuf Oreo.

-No way!
I wonder if we're related.

a daughter who was a kitten
and a son?

The son they had--
what did he turn out to be?

-Right, but I mean,
was he a bunny? A flower?

-Hey, kiddo! See you at
the reunion this summer?

-Whoa! You two have the
craziest family tree ever!

-Everybody barfs glitter
out of sheer happiness.

-Weird. I usually just barf
glitter out of my mouth.

-Do you know who our great-
great-GREAT-grandparents were?
-Sure do! She was a Tootsie Roll

and he was the
essence of wonder!

-And he was born to Christmas
spirit and a child's laughter!

-And just because I'm confused,
Marshmallow, what about you?

Are you the son of a unicorn
or the daughter of a unicorn?

-You know,
I get asked this a lot.

Time to put it to rest
once and for all.

I'm a--
-I hate to cut in, but...

-Wow.
Guy really had a lot of guts.

[laughs briefly]
Sorry, I couldn't help myself.
Aah, it's coming for all of us!

-Orange! We have to save Gilly!
She's family!

-You're right.
-Hurry, we need a plan fast.

-Oh, I know. We'll hire a lawyer
and sue their pants off.

-[in agony]:
Oh! I feel everything! Aah...!

-We have to do something!
-Ooh-ooh, I can motorboat.

-Aw. Uh-oh, Gilly,
I think you're gonna die.

-So long, Marshmallow.
See you next reunion.

And bye-bye to you, O-range.
[chimes away]

-Wow! I guess her mama
really was a rainbow.

I figured the trout saying
that for the "halibut." [laughs]

-Oh, Orange, I'm so happy,
I could just--
